# AI Museum Curator â€” Greek Mythology Edition

This Streamlit app allows users to explore Greek gods, heroes, and mythic creatures through major artworks, manuscripts, books, and cultural artifacts. Optional AI features provide curator-level explanations.

## Features

### Home
- Paste your OpenAI API Key to enable AI features.
- Step-by-step guide for exploring Greek mythology content and artworks.
- Instructions for viewing detailed work cards with AI-generated descriptions.

### Greek Deities / Heroes / Creatures
- Search or select mythic figures.
- Default display of the most famous works related to the figure (artworks, manuscripts, books).
- Works are shown in card/grid style with expandable details.
- AI-generated overview, historical/artistic context, and iconography.

### Interactive Art Zone
- **Myth-based**: Describe a scene or motif, get the most likely Greek myth character.
- **Personality Archetype Matcher**: Short quiz mapping you to a Greek myth archetype.
- Category selection presented as clear small cards.

### Big Data Analysis
- **Time dimension**: Work distribution by century/era, artist active period trends.
- **Medium/type dimension**: Cross-medium distribution, material analysis.
- **Style/genre**: Artistic style distribution, association of style with mythic themes.

### Notes
- Works failing to load (HTTP 404 or other errors) are automatically skipped.
- Interactive and AI features require an OpenAI API key.
